definition.value: An organic sodium salt which is the tetrasodium salt of eritoran.
A compound derived from a hydrocarbon by replacing one or more hydrogen atoms with fluorine atoms.

A  catecholamine that is 4-(3-aminobutyl)phenol in which one of the hydrogens attached to the nitrogen is substituted by a 2-(3,4-dihydroxyphenyl)ethyl group. A beta1-adrenergic receptor agonist that has cardiac stimulant action without evoking vasoconstriction or tachycardia, it is used as the hydrochloride to increase the contractility of the heart in the management of acute heart failure.
Compounds based on a fused 1,2- or 1,3-oxazole and benzene bicyclic ring skeleton.
An octene with an unsaturation C-1.

The hydrochloride salt of dobutamine.  A beta1-adrenergic receptor agonist that has cardiac stimulant action without evoking vasoconstriction or tachycardia, it is used to increase the contractility of the heart in the management of acute heart failure.
Any mineral that contains sulfide (S(2-)) as the major anion.
A salt in which the anionic species is sulfide (S(2-)).
A tetracyclic diterpenoid that is paclitaxel with the N-benzyloxycarbonyl group replaced by N-tert-butoxycarbonyl, and the acetoxy group at position 10 replaced by a hydroxy group.
Any carbonate that is carbonic acid in which the hydrogens have been replaced by organyl groups.
A mineral that is composed of atoms from a single element.
A germacrane sesquiterpenoid obtained from germacrane by hydroxylation at C(11) together with dehydrogenation across the C(1)-C(10) and C(5)-C(6) bonds.
